- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on formalization and verification of a safety-critical system standard, which is a key aspect of software engineering.
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is also likely as the paper specifically deals with the ARINC 653 standard, which is a real-time operating system standard.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper uses the Event-B formal reasoning approach, which is a formal language for specifying and verifying software systems.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is another possible category as the paper uses formal reasoning techniques to verify the correctness of the ARINC 653 standard.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with safety-critical systems, which often have security implications.
